er;\"| {{font color|white|Ghost}}\n|align=center| [[#Golurk|Golurk (#623)]]\n|rowspan=2| Golett and Golurk are among the first Pok\u00e9mon to be designed by a Western artist.<ref name=\"GolettCreator\">{{cite web|publisher=Lava Cut Content|accessdate=May 26, 2019|title=Ken Sugimori Reveals Beta Pok\u00e9mon Info (Gen 5)|url=http://lavacutcontent.com/ken-sugimori-nintendo-dream/}}</ref> Golurk's design is inspired by the [[Golem of Prague]] of [[Jewish folklore]], a clay figure given life to protect the Jewish people of Prague from attacks and persecution.<ref name=\"GR_myth\">{{cite web|author=Lucas Sullivan|work=[[GamesRadar]]|publisher=[[Future plc]]|date=February 8, 2014|accessdate=January 27, 2016|title=17 Pokemon based on real-world mythology|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/15-pokemon-based-real-world-mythology/}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{anchor|Golurk}} Golurk\n!scope=\"row\"| {{nihongo||\u30b4\u30eb\u30fc\u30b0|Gor\u016bgu}}\n|align=center| {{nts|623}}\n| style=\"background:#e0c068; text-align:center;\"| Ground\n| style=\"background:#614c83; text-align:center;\"| {{font color|white|Ghost}}\n| {{n/a|Does not evolve}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{anchor|Pawniard}} Pawniard\n!scope=\"row\"| {{nihongo||\u30b3\u30de\u30bf\u30ca|Komatana}}\n|align=center| {{nts|624}}\n| style=\"background:#5c483b; text-align:center;\"| {{font color|white|Dark}}\n| style=\"background:#b8b8d0; text-align:center;\"| Steel\n|align=center| [[#Bisharp|Bisharp (#625)]]\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{anchor|Bisharp}} Bisharp\n!scope=\"row\"| {{nihongo||\u30ad\u30ea\u30ad\u30b6\u30f3|Kirikizan}}\n|align=center| {{nts|625}}\n| style=\"background:#5c483b; text-align:center;\"| {{font color|white|Dark}}\n| style=\"background:#b8b8d0; text-align:center;\"| Steel\n| {{n/a|Does not evolve}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| {{anchor|Bouffalant}} Bouffalant\n!scope=\"row\"| {{nihongo||\u30d0\u30c3\u30d5\u30ed\u30f3|Baffuron}}\n|align=center| {{nts|626}}\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#a8a878; text-align:center