 California]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Crips]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Long Beach, California]]\n[[Category:West Coast hip hop musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male musicians]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n\n\n{{US-hiphop-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = O.T. Genasis\n| background = solo_singer\n| image = Ot-genasis-vibe-interview-560x560.jpg\n| caption = O.T. Genasis in 2015\n| birth_name = Odis Oliver Flores\n| alias = O.T. Genasis\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1987|6|18}}\n| birth_place = [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], U.S.\n| origin = [[Long Beach, California]], U.S.\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Trap music|trap]]\n}}\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n* Rapper\n* songwriter\n}}\n| years_active = 2011\u2013present\n| label = {{flatlist|\n* Fast Lyfe\n* [[Conglomerate (record label)|Conglomerate]]\n* [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n*[[Busta Rhymes]]\n*[[G-Unit]]\n*[[K Camp]]\n*[[Young Dolph]]\n}}\n| website = {{URL|otgenasis.com}}\n}}\n'''Odis Oliver Flores''' (born June 18, 1987), better known by the [[stage name]] '''O.T. Genasis''', is an American rapper and songwriter.\n\n==Early life==\nOdis Oliver Flores was born on June 18, 1987 in [[Atlanta]] to [[Belizeans|Belizean]] immigrants. He is West Indian American. He grew up in [[Long Beach, California]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/ot-genasis-mn0003312016/biography | title=O.T. Genasis biography | publisher=[[AllMusic]] | accessdate=}}</ref> Genasis states that his influences include [[Cutty Ranks]], [[Buju Banton]], [[T.I.]], [[Ludacris]], [[Tupac Shakur]], [[Shabba Ranks]], and [[50 Cent]].{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n==Career==\nIn 2011, [[G-Unit Records]] signed him to their label. In 2012, under his association with G-Unit, he released his untitled debut official mixtape. He later was signed to [[Busta Rhymes]]' [[Conglomerate (record label)|Conglomerate Records]]. After being signed to a Conglomerate label, he has been putting out some songs and singles such as \"Touchdown (Remix)\" featuring Busta Rhymes and [[French Montana]], and \"[[CoCo (O.T. Genasis song)|CoCo]]\". The former single became a successful song to chart, peaking at number 20 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. [[Beyonc\u00e9]] used his song Everybody Mad as part of her [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival|Coachella]] 2018 performance and as part of her and Jay-Z [[On the Run II Tour]].\n\n==Personal life==\nFlores is a father to son, Genasis Flores who was born on March 25, 2010. In a 2016 interview with [[The Shade Room]], OT stated his son has autism. On March 14, 2020, Flores and Malika Haqq - a TV personality - delivered their baby boy Ace Flores. <ref>https://people.com/parents/exes-malika-haqq-and-ot-genasis-confirm-rapper-is-the-baby-boys-father/</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of mixtapes, with year released\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Black Belt''\n|\n* Released: June 13, 2012\n* Label: [[G-Unit Records|G-Unit]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Catastrophic 2''<br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(with [[Busta Rhymes]] and J-Doe)</span>\n|\n* Released: August 7, 2014\n* Label: [[Conglomerate (record label)|Conglomerate]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''Rhythm & Bricks''\n|\n* Released: September 22, 2015\n* Label: Conglomerate\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Coke N Butter]]''\n|\n* Released: November 11, 2016\n* Label: Conglomerate\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions and certifications, showing year released and album name\n! sc